statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.description: The total number of rebounds (offensive and defensive).

article.headline: Lamar 88, Huston-Tillotson 59
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas -- Anthony Miles scored 18 points and Mike James added 16 to lead Lamar to an 88-59 victory against Huston-Tillotson on Wednesday night. Tre Lynch had 12 points and Brandon Davis 10 for the Cardinals (7-3). Ronzelle Fort scored 19 points and Lance Richardson had 10 points and 12 rebounds for Huston-Tillotson (0-8), an NAIA school in Austin, Texas, that classified the game as an exhibition. The Rams' record remained 0-7. Playing its third game in five days, Huston-Tillotson led 26-25 before going scoreless for a 5:11 stretch covering the end of the first half and start of the second. Lamar took advantage, building a 42-27 cushion. Davis' jumper gave the Cardinals a 67-37 lead with 9:37 remaining.
